Subject: Hodge Cycle Output Admission Ledger

Description: Project-local math inquiry tool for admitting or rejecting Hodge construction mechanisms as actual algebraic-cycle output for arbitrary rational Hodge classes.

& [HodgeCycleOutputAdmissionLedger] is a math inquiry tool
  + [tool_uuid] is 8f4f65e7-1e48-4dfb-b124-26d0b55d0484
  + [project] is seven math problems
  + [problem] is Hodge Conjecture
  + [created_at] is 2026-06-26
  + [trigger_record] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\events\project_reflections\2026-06-26_navier_stokes_theta_reentry_saturation_reflection_001.sop
  + [role] is test whether a Hodge mechanism outputs algebraic cycles for arbitrary rational Hodge-class input
  + [not_role] is proving Hodge, accepting detection as construction, or treating substitute structures as algebraic cycles

& [AdmissionColumnSet] is the cycle-output surface
  + [candidate_mechanism] is the construction, correspondence, spread, normal-function, motive, or algorithm candidate
  + [input_class_scope] is arbitrary_rational_hodge_class, family_class, special_locus_class, correspondence_supplied, motivated_class, or unclear
  + [output_object] is algebraic_cycle, cycle_class_after_transfer, detected_locus, obstruction_invariant, substitute_structure, or none
  + [output_effectivity] is explicit_cycle, existential_cycle, conditional_cycle, transfer_if_correspondence_given, detection_only, or absent
  + [arbitrary_scope_status] is arbitrary, family_scoped, special_locus_only, correspondence_scoped, substitute_only, or absent
  + [cohomology_match_status] is proves_class_match, conditional_match, detects_possible_match, substitute_match, unknown, or none
  + [authority_status] is admitted_for_line_audit, boundary_only, deep_research_needed, rejected_as_authority, or outside
  + [first_missing_feature] is the earliest missing feature blocking proof-shaped promotion

& [UseProcedure] is the admission workflow
  + [step_001_name_candidate] is identify the mechanism and its allowed input data
  + [step_002_output] is decide whether it outputs an algebraic cycle or only detects, organizes, substitutes, or transfers
  + [step_003_scope] is test whether the mechanism handles arbitrary rational classes or only special/family/correspondence-supplied cases
  + [step_004_match] is test whether the output cycle class is proved to match the input Hodge class
  + [step_005_admit] is admit only mechanisms with enough cycle output and matching structure for line-by-line audit

  = must: require algebraic-cycle output or a theorem forcing algebraic-cycle existence
  = must: separate "correspondence supplied" from "correspondence generated"
  = must: reject normal-function or Noether-Lefschetz detection as arbitrary-cycle construction
  = should: preserve scoped mechanisms as calibration when they teach proof shape
  - never: count motivated, absolute, integral, or Kahler substitute frameworks as Clay-target output without algebraic cycles

(hodge_cycle_output_admission_ledger) :candidate_mechanism: /input scope, output object, effectivity, arbitrary scope, cohomology match/ |Hodge proof|
  + [inside] is admission control for explicit Hodge cycle-construction audits
  + [boundary] is a candidate must output cycles for arbitrary rational Hodge classes or generate correspondences that do so
  |outside| detection-only tools, special-family calibration, substitute structures, and correspondence transfer without generated correspondences

